race.comment: Hard to fault the form of SH'BOURNE MIDNIGHT (1) who has a great overall record including two wins and two minors from five tries this course and distance. Just missed fresh then scored over 1420m latest and drawn for a good run will go close again. STONE COLD STUNNER (10) made a nice return over 1200m when placed and strips fitter. Has placed 2/3 second-up and should be in the finish again. FIGHTING FLOYD (7) was a winner in slightly easier grade last time. Has great stats at the course and distance and with the claimer aboard again drops nicely in the weights. RUBBLE 'N' FUDD (9) is a bit of an enigma boasting plenty of talent but has struggled to put it on the board. Just missed two back then well off best latest. Has trialled since and scratched Friday and saved for this. Have to include. FLOSSING (11) is a former  Victorian having first run this area and could easily measure up on best figures.
